Package: routlier
Type: Package
Title: Highlights outliers in a dataset
Version: 0.1.2
Authors@R: c(
    person("Ben", "Gonzalez", , "gonzalezben393@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0009-0008-6307-5161")))
Maintainer: Ben Gonzalez<gonzalezben393@gmail.com>
Description: Allows an individual to highlight outliers in a dataset. The outliers are highlighted in green and replaced with the word outlier. This allows an individual to easily identify an outlier and continue or correct the problem. The outlier that is detected is 3 standard deviations from the mean of the data that is being utilized.
URL: https://github.com/gonzalezben81/routlier
BugReports: https://github.com/gonzalezben81/routlier/issues
License: GPL-3
Depends: R (>= 3.5.0)
Encoding: UTF-8
Imports: rhandsontable, dplyr, DT, formattable
SystemRequirements: qpdf (for optimizing PDF files)
Suggests: knitr, rmarkdown
VignetteBuilder: knitr
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 7.3.1
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
